   <h1>Teacher Pack</h1>
<p>
    These activities are designed to teach computational thinking at different stages of the software process aimed at KS2, age 7-11.
    For each activity there are varying lengthed activities with lesson plans, designed to help you plan and assess learning.
    <br />I ask that you do whatever you can of these to help me with my research.
    <br />Activity 1: 40 minutes, the basic activity to try.
    <br />Activity 2: 15 minutes, a simple starter activity.
    <br />Activity 3: 2 x 40 minutes, maybe only for those really interested, similar in style to Activity 1
    <br />Activity 4: 5 x 40 minutes, a big project, if you are interested get in touch and I'd be delightd to support you.
    <br />Each activity has an accompanying worksheet to be filled out as the lesson progresses. For those participating in my research I will collect these.
    <br />Children may work in pairs or singly, but each should fill out their own worksheet.
    <br /><br /><i>If you would like to participate in the research and have not already been in touch, please <a href="mailto:rachelalcraft@gmail.com">email me.</i></a>
</p>

