<h3>Activity 1: Simple Simon Game Design</h3>
<p><i>The online-only activity requires a computers (as opposed to a tablet) as it uses an embedded scratch project which needs support for </i></p>
<p>In this activity children are presented with a badly designed game that is unplayable. 
    Using a design studio within the webpage they can change the layout and colours to create a redesign
    that turns the game into something playable with no code changes.
    This activity teaches the children about user experience, 
    and how design crucially influences the usability of a software artefact.</p>
<p>       
